ZCZC RE05
080250 UTC JAN 22
GREENLAND VIA SAUDANES
A LOW 960 HPA SOUTHEAST OF CAPE FAREWELL IS MOVING TOWARDS NORTHEAST
AND GIVES SNOW AND SLEET TO THE EASTERN AND SOUTHEASTERN WATERS. IN WESTERN
AND SOUTHERN WATERS NORTHWESTERLY FLOW OF COLD AIR MASS WITH SNOW OR SNOW
SHOWERS BUT DURING SATURDAY SEVERAL MINOR LOW WILL FORM AND GIVES CONTINUE
TO SNOW AND SNOW SHOWERS.
SATURDAY NOON A LOW 975 HPA IS EXPECTED NEAR NEWFOUNDLAND.
THE LOW WILL MOVE TOWARDS NORTHEAST AND WILL SATURDAY EVENING GIVE WIDESPREAD
SNOW AND SLEET TO THE SOUTHERN WATERS.
